module.exports = `<p><span><u><span style="color: windowtext;">Lecture</span></u></span><span><span style="color: windowtext;">: TR 12:30 -1:45pm; Room 22 ten Hoor</span></span></p><p><span><strong><span style="color: windowtext;"> </span></strong></span></p><p><span><strong><span style="color: windowtext;">Course Description:</span></strong></span> <span style="color: windowtext;">This class will provide an overview of the prehistory, history, and modern day cultural diversity of Native Americans throughout North America. Social, economic, and technological developments of different native groups are explored including changes as a result of European contact and recent attempts to revitalize Native American culture. </span><span style="color: windowtext;"> In this course, </span><span style="color: windowtext;">the traditional and contemporary lifeways of North American Indian tribes from eleven different culture areas are presented. Students will develop critical thinking skills by analyzing and evaluating the geographical, economic, and cultural adaptations of each region.</span></p><p><span style="color: black;"> </span></p><p><strong>Course Prerequisites/Corequisites:</strong> None</p><p> </p><p><strong>Learning Outcomes:</strong> Upon the completion of this course, students should be able to:</p><ol><li> Explain the trajectory of <span style="color: black;">technological and cultural developments of prehistoric Native Americas prior to European contact</span></li><li> <span style="color: black;">Describe changes in Native American technology and social organization as a result of European contact</span></li><li> <span style="color: black;">Recall the names, locations, and geography of the 11 Native America culture areas of North America</span></li><li> Define the different Native America culture areas and describe differences between the Native Americans of these areas in terms of their environment, technology, and social organization</li></ol>`;
